Phase 1: Target Intel
Goal: Discover the company's ecosystem — domains, products, acquisitions, tech stack.
Tools:
whois target.com – Get admin emails, registration dates
SecurityTrails – DNS history, subdomain changes
curl https://crt.sh/?q=%.target.com&output=json – Discover subdomains via SSL certs
Hunter.io – Discover employee emails
Google Dorks

✅ Phase 2: Subdomain Enumeration 
Tools:
amass enum -passive -d target.com -o amass.txt
assetfinder --subs-only target.com > assetfinder.txt
subfinder -d target.com -o subfinder.txt
crt.sh, dnsdumpster, waybackurls

Merge and dedup:
cat *.txt | sort -u > all_subs.txt

✅ Phase 3: Live Host Discovery
Tools:
httpx -l all_subs.txt -status-code -title -tech-detect -o live_hosts.txt
nmap -iL live_hosts.txt -Pn -sS -T4 -p- -oN nmap_full.txt

✅ Phase 4: Endpoint Discovery ( Discover hidden, deprecated, or vulnerable endpoints.)
Tools:
waybackurls
gau
katana
ffuf -u https://target.com/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt -mc all

✅ Phase 5: Vulnerability Scanning

Tools:
nuclei -l live_hosts.txt -t cves/ -o nuclei_cves.txt
nuclei -l all_urls.txt -t vulnerabilities/ -o web_vulns.txt
jaeles scan -s signatures/ -u https://target.com
dalfox -b your.collaborator -w all_urls.txt

